Programs
1) Java method with no parameters returning integer value
class Test {

    int getNumber() {

        return 100;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Test t = new Test();

        System.out.println(t.getNumber());

    }
}
Output
100
2) Static method taking two numbers and returning their sum
class Test {

    static int add(int a, int b) {

        return a + b;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        System.out.println(Test.add(10, 20));

    }
}
Output
30
3) Public method returning string message
class Test {

    public String message() {

        return "Welcome to Java";
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Test t = new Test();

        System.out.println(t.message());

    }
}
Output
Welcome to Java
4) Method printing message without returning value
class Test {

    void display() {

        System.out.println("Hello Java");

    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Test t = new Test();

        t.display();

    }
}
Important Point
void

means:

No return value
5) Method accepting parameters, performing calculation, and returning result
class Test {

    int multiply(int a, int b) {

        return a * b;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Test t = new Test();

        System.out.println(t.multiply(5, 4));

    }
}
Output

20
